<h2>Millrise Homes</h2>
<p>A suburban community in southwest Calgary, Millrise was established in 1982, though it was annexed by the city in 1961 as part of the Area Structure Plan, aka Midnapore Phase II. Millrise is a simple, quiet community with fresh air and rich green vegetation. With many to do around and easy access to public transport, Millrise is an ideal place for those who love a quiet place in the suburbs.</p>
<h2>Millrise Real Estate Listings Community #153</h2>
<p>Calgary Real Estate Quadrant: SouthWest Calgary<br />Similar neighboring communities of <a href="/shawnessy.php" target="_self">Shawnessy</a> and <a href="/midnapore.php" target="_self">Midnapore</a>.<br />Community Established 1982 <br /><br />Originally this section of Calgary real estate was to be phase II of Midnapore in 1982 development began under the name and community of Millrise. Homes for sale in this Caglary district lie in a suburban community of predominantly single-family residential homes. The neighbourhood is close to major roadways, and to Fish Creek Provincial Park and its related amenities. The C-Train runs through Millrise to the Somerset Station.<br /><br /><strong>Millrise Schools</strong><br />Our Lady of Peace Elementary &amp; Junior High &ndash; Separate<br /><br /></p>
<h2>Millrise Real Estate Market</h2>
<p>As of the year 2000, approximately 24.7% of Millrise homes were apartments and condominiums and 13.2% of housing was for rental use. The residential homes are single-family detached homes, in bungalow and two-storey style. Average property price is $362 522.</p>
